\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. R. wettsteinii} (Sterneck) Soó, {\i Feddes Repert}.{\b  26}: 182 (1929).Stem 10-20 cm, simple or branched, densely glandular-pubescent, without black streaks. Leaves lanceolate, with remote, acute teeth. Bracts exceeding calyx, triangular, densely glandular-pubescent; teeth patent, the proximal nearly twice as long as the distal. Calyx densely glandular-pubescent. Corolla c. 18 mm; throat more or less closed. •{\i  C. & S. Appennini.} It.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. R. pubescens} (Sterneck) Boiss. & Heldr. ex Soó,{\i  op. cit.} 206 (1929) ({\i Alectorolophus pubescens} Sterneck). Like {\b 4} but stem up to 40 cm; leaves oblong, crenate-serrate; bracts scarcely exceeding calyx. with appressed teeth. •{\i  Mountains of Greece}. Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. R. pindicus} (Sterneck) Soó,{\i  Izv. Bot. Inst.} ({\i Sofia}){\b  6}: 367 (1958) ({\i Alectorolophus pindicus} Sterneck). Like {\b 4} but bracts and calyx glabrous, except for scabrid margin and teeth. •{\i  N.C. Greece.} Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  {\b R. sintenisii} (Sterneck) Soó,{\i  loc. cit.} (1958) ({\i Alectorolophus sintenisii} Sterneck) from N.C. Greece (near Malakasi) is also like {\b 4} but with bracts and calyx subglabrous except for densely glandular margins and teeth; but it has conical teeth on the upper lip of the corolla c. 2 mm long and its systematic position must, therefore, be considered doubtful.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. R. antiquus} (Sterneck) Schinz & Thell. in Schinz & R.Keller,{\i  Fl. Schweiz} ed. 3,{\b  2}: 315 (1914) ({\i Alectorolophus antiquus} Sterneck). Stem 5-15 cm, usually simple, without black streaks. Leaves ovate to lanceolate, acutely serrate. Bracts glabrous, triangular-ovate, acuminate; teeth abruptly diminishing in length towards apex, the basal up to 6 mm, acute but not aristate. Calyx glabrous. Corolla c. 15 mm; tube somewhat curved; throat more or less closed. •{\i  S. Alps}. He It.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. ANOMALI (Sterneck) Soó. Upper lip of corolla with convex margins and with teeth 1·5-2·5 mm, 2-3 times as long as wide; throat open.
