\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. R. dinaricus} Murb.,{\i  Lunds Univ. Årsskr.}{\b  27}({\b 5}): 69 (1892) ({\i Alectorolophus dinaricus} (Murb.) Sterneck; incl.{\i  R. praesignis} (G. Beck & Sterneck) Soó). Stem up to 30 cm, branched, without black streaks. Leaves lanceolate, remotely serrate. Bracts slightly exceeding calyx, glabrous, triangular-ovate; teeth acute, not aristate, gradually diminishing in length towards apex. Calyx glabrous or puberulent. Corolla c. 20 mm; tube straight. •{\i  W.C. Jugoslavia} ({\i Bosna, Hercegovina}). Ju.
\par

