\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. R. aristatus} Celak.,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr. }{\b 20}: 132 (1870) ({\i R. angustifolius} auct., non C. C. Gmelin,{\i  Alectorolophus angustifolius} auct., non (C.C. Gmelin) Heynh.; incl.{\i  R. lanceolatus} (Kováts ex Neilr.) Chab.). Stem 5-50 cm, simple or branched, glabrous or subglabrous, with black streaks. Leaves linear to lanceolate, crenate-serrate. Bracts slightly exceeding calyx, glabrous, narrowly triangular, the basal 3-4 teeth subulate, aristate, the others much shorter, shortly aristate. Calyx glabrous. Corolla 15-18 mm; tube abruptly curved. 2n = 22. •{\i  S.C. Europe, extending to S.E. France and S. W. Jugoslavia.} Au Cz Ga Ge He It Ju.
